definition.value: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine having palmitoyl and 5-oxovaleryl groups at the 1- and 2-positions respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-[omega-(acylyloxy)]acylsphin-4-enine in which the omega-O-acyl group is specified as  (9R,10R)-epoxy-(13R)-hydroxy-(11E)-octadecenoyl (R represents a very long chain acyl group).
An N-[omega-(acylyloxy)]acylsphin-4-enine in which the omega-O-acyl group is specified as (9R,10R)-epoxy-13-keto-(11E)-octadecenoyl (R represents a very long chain acyl group).
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-(4-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-5-yl)propanoic acid and the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An aci-nitro compound that is the predominant form of ethylnitronate at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A hydroxy fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of 9(R)-HODE; major species at pH 7.3.

A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion that is the tetraanion of 8-oxo-dGTP arising from deprotonation of the triphosphate OH groups. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion that is the tetraanion of 2'-deoxy-2-hydroxyadenosine 5'-triphosphate, arising from deprotonation of the triphosphate OH groups. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A member of the class of imidazoles that comprises 2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethylimidazole carrying an additional (2-chloro-3-thienyl)methoxy substituent at position 2.
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 2-hydroxy group of (S)-averantin. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A citrate salt which comprises equimolar amounts of orphenadrine and citric acid.
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 2-hydroxy group of (1'S,5'S)-5'-hydroxyaverantin. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

An oxonium betaine that is the conjugate base of any anthocyanidin 3-O-[2-O-(4-coumaroyl)-alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucoside] 5-O-beta-D-glucoside and is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed from (allyl 7-azido-3,7-dideoxy-beta-L-gulo-oct-2-ulopyranosid)onic acid by proton loss from the carboxy group.
A 1-{2-[(2-chloro-3-thienyl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of tioconazole.
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 2-hydroxy group of norsolorinic acid anthrone. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A 1-{2-[(2-chloro-3-thienyl)methoxy]-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of tioconazole.
A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the 2-hydroxy group to the 1-amino group of minocycline. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 8-hydroxy group of hydroxyversicolorone. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A tetracyclic diterpenoid that is a semisynthetic analogue of sordadin. It has a tetracyclic diterpene glycoside structure.
The sodium salt of (allyl 3-deoxy-7-O-methyl-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranosid)onic acid.
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed from (allyl 3-deoxy-7-O-methyl-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranosid)onic acid by proton loss from the carboxy group.
The carbohydrate acid derivative that is the allyl glycoside of 7-O-methyl-Kdo.
An organic sodium salt that is the monosodium salt of mutalomycin.
A HPETE anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of 9(R)-HPETE; major species at pH 7.3.
An alkene that is but-1-ene carrying a methyl substituent at position 3.
An alkene that is but-1-ene carrying a methyl substituent at position 2.
An alkene that is ethylene in which three of the hydrogens are replaced by methyl groups.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of mutalomycin, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A polyether antibiotic produced by a strain of Streptomyces mutabilis NRRL 8088.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (7R)-hydroxy-(5S,6S)-epoxy-(8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A sterol ester that is the 3-hexanoyl derivative of (24S)-24-hydroxycholesterol.

A macrolide antibiotic that is a semisynthetic analogue of concanamycin A, possessing an 18-membered lactone ring and a 6-membered oxane ring in which the hydroxy group at position 23 is glycosylated by a 4-O-carbamoyl-2,6-dideoxy-beta-D-arabino-hexopyranosyl residue.
An enol that is 3-methylbut-1-ene in which one of the terminal hydrogens is replaced by a hydroxy group.

The sodium salt of a carbohydrate lactone formed from alpha-Kdo-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-OAll by lactone formation between the carboxy group of the non-reducing alpha-Kdo residue and O-7 of the alpha-Kdo-OAll residue.
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed by proton loss from the carboxy group of alpha-Kdo-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-OAll II(1),I(7)-lactone
A carbohydrate lactone formed from alpha-Kdo-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-OAll by lactone formation between the carboxy group of the non-reducing alpha-Kdo residue and O-7 of the alpha-Kdo-OAll residue.
A methyl ketone that is nonane in which the methylene hydrogens at position 2 are replaced by an oxo group.
A methyl ketone that is tridecane in which the methylene hydrogens at position 2 are replaced by an oxo group.
A methyl ketone that is decane in which the methylene hydrogens at position 2 are replaced by an oxo group.
A secondary alcohol that is undecane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.

A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5- and 7-hydroxy groups of cyanidin 3-O-[6-O-(6-O-4-hydroxycinnamoyl-beta-D-glucosyl)-2-O-beta-D-xylosyl-beta-D-galactoside]. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the 2-hydroxy group to the 1-amino group of tetracycline. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 2-hydroxy group of (S)-5'-oxoaverantin. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An icosanoid anion that is the conjugate base of 8(S)-HETE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5- and 7-hydroxy groups of cyanidin 3-O-beta-D-galactoside. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A member of the class of furans that is 2-furoic acid in which the hydrogen at position 5 is replaced by a tetradecyloxy group.

The sodium salt of alpha-Kdo1Me-(2->8)-alpha-Kdo-OAll, a disaccharide derivative consisting of two 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranonosyl units joined via an alpha-(2->8)-linkage with an O-allyl group at the anomeric centre and with the carboxy group of the residue at the non-reducing end methyl-esterified.
An organic anion obtained by removal of one of the methylene protons from barbituric acid. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A flavonoid oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group of oroxylin A. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
